	(text "- Chip runs on 3V, and is as such powered by the LDO below\n- Capacitors C[43..48] are for all VCC pins in pairs of 4.7u and 100n. Place them close to the\n   power pins for decoupling.\n- SIO[0..7] are Serial Input/Output pins, and have to be length matched to within 50 mils, and \n   also impedance matched to 50 Ohms for single-ended t-lines and 100 Ohms for differential\n   pairs.\n- All pins are active-low, and thus the required ones are pulled high.\n- TVS clamping voltage must not exceed 3v3\n- All resistors are 0805 imperial\n- NC pins have been remapped ONLY FOR ROUTING PURPOSES!!!"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 163.83 100.076 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
				(thickness 0.1588)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "22f84d7b-d395-471e-a4da-2f8bf5e7320f")
	)
